  "reveal": {
    "brief_voiced": "Fifi Swain rang Caritas, the third bell, and at the tenth change her hands left the rope. The touch had faltered once before—the Colonel's grip on Fides at the first change, a green hand's stumble that convicts nobody—but when Caritas fell out of true in the third minute, those hands were elsewhere, occupied with murder. The rope lay slack in her absence.\n\nFifi, a lady's-maid, hears more than a servant ought. Xerxes Hartfield was a gentleman of great fortune and few explanations, untroubled at any table. What she heard, what silence bought, what fortune stood between them, the tower keeps to itself. But her hands know when they held the rope, and when they did not.\n\nThe bell does not lie.",
